task.summary: Merged your changes and my changes to the panel class and fixed a few problems that I had when moving pieces. Also temporarily changed layout so we could test it
Merged your changes and my changes to the panel class and fixed a few problems that I had when moving pieces. Also temporarily changed layout so we could test it
Merged your changes and my changes to the panel class and fixed a few problems that I had when moving pieces. Also temporarily changed layout so we could test it

Fixed the Rook's movements(changed ifs and loops to four separate cases: up, down, right, or left), changed players after movment so only one can go at a time (starts with white), included a border so that you can see when you've selected a piece, changed isValidMove for ChessPiece to allow for captures, and fixed pawn's movement when capturing
I added a blue border around possible move locations. Reveals some issues that still need to be ironed out. Committing so you can test with it if you want

I got the rook working and added an undo button to the jmenubar (temporarily). I added undo functionality and got it working with regular moves and captures. I added en passant for the pawn (it's a special move in chess) and got it to work with undo.

I got the rook working and added an undo button to the jmenubar (temporarily). I added undo functionality and got it working with regular moves and captures. I added en passant for the pawn (it's a special move in chess) and got it to work with undo.

I added an undo button to the jmenubar (temporarily). I added undo functionality and got it working with regular moves and captures. I added en passant for the pawn (it's a special move in chess) and got it to work with undo.

I got inCheck working and added a method that returns an array of moves that will escape check. I set the actionlistener up so that a player in check must get out of check and the board highlights pieces differently when a piece is in check.

I changed isValidMove to include returning false if a move will put the player in check. I had to change a lot of code layout to get this implemented, so I removed the capturing method and just included it in the move method, and changed the method that made an array of possible moves. I added a method that sorts through the array of possible moves and removes moves that put a player in check. I had to separate these (unfortunately). I also changed the actionlistener so that not being able to put yourself in check would not be prevented there, but only verified.

The king and the rook can now castle. The only thing that still needs to be fixed is that when a castle move is undone, the stack does not know that a castle was done, and thus cannot allow for it to be done after the undo.
I moved the timer panel to the menu bar. This fixed my issue with window resizing.
I added a method in the AI class so that the AI would try to get out of check.
